<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,829,1178]" box="[199,1345,901,926]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,901,926]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Distribution.</emphasis>
Endemic species with the only known record from a waterfall in central Zagros (
<figureCitation box="[1262,1328,901,925]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1569,1592]" captionTargetBox="[196,1361,337,1474]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,261,1546]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 1. Distribution map of freshwater Gammarus species in Iran (grey regions indicate high mountainous areas)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205632/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[1315,1328,901,925]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,829,1178]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,377,937,962]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Ecologic notes.</emphasis>
The species lives in high mountains of ca. 
<quantity box="[869,955,937,961]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="m" value="2100.0">2100 m</quantity>
asl. It was found under aquatic vegetation and in a gravel bed (
<bibRefCitation author="Khalaji-Pirbalouty" box="[378,744,973,997]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refString="Khalaji-Pirbalouty, V. &amp; Sari, A. (2006) A Description of Gammarus baloutchi n. sp. (Amphipoda: Gammaridae) from Iran, based on light and electron microscopy. Zoologische Mededelingen (Leiden), 80 1 (6), 91 - 100." type="journal article" year="2006">
Khalaji-Pirbalouty &amp; Sari, 
<number box="[683,744,973,997]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,829,1178]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,450,1009,1034]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Taxonomic remarks.</emphasis>
Among Iranian 
<taxonomicName box="[651,776,1010,1033]" class="Malacostraca" family="Gammaridae" genus="Gammarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[651,776,1010,1033]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Gammarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, the short endopodite of uropod 
<number box="[1269,1283,1009,1033]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="3.0">3</number>
can only be observed in 
<taxonomicName box="[287,423,1045,1069]" class="Malacostraca" family="Gammaridae" genus="Gammarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baloutchi">
<emphasis box="[287,423,1045,1069]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">G. baloutchi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[436,538,1045,1069]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">G. l o b i f e r</emphasis>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[601,757,1045,1069]" class="Malacostraca" family="Gammaridae" genus="Gammarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sepidannus">
<emphasis box="[601,757,1045,1069]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">G. sepidannus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The first species can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName box="[1255,1360,1045,1069]" class="Malacostraca" family="Gammaridae" genus="Gammarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lobifer">
<emphasis box="[1255,1360,1045,1069]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">G. lobifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the lack of the sub-angular setae on basis of pereopod 
<number box="[732,746,1082,1105]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="7.0">7</number>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Khalaji-Pirbalouty" box="[762,1231,1081,1105]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refString="Khalaji-Pirbalouty, V. &amp; Sari, A. (2006) A Description of Gammarus baloutchi n. sp. (Amphipoda: Gammaridae) from Iran, based on light and electron microscopy. Zoologische Mededelingen (Leiden), 80 1 (6), 91 - 100." type="journal article" year="2006">
Khalaji-Pirbalouty and Sari, 
<number box="[1091,1149,1081,1105]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="2006.0">2006</number>
, Fig. 
<number box="[1216,1231,1081,1105]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="3.0">3</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), shorter antennal gland cone, and longer setation of peduncle segments of antenna 
<number box="[890,904,1117,1141]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="2.0">2</number>
(
<emphasis box="[921,965,1117,1141]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">ibid</emphasis>
. 
<figureCitation box="[980,1045,1117,1141]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1569,1592]" captionTargetBox="[196,1361,337,1474]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,261,1546]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 1. Distribution map of freshwater Gammarus species in Iran (grey regions indicate high mountainous areas)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205632/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[1032,1045,1117,1141]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). From 
<taxonomicName box="[1139,1296,1117,1141]" class="Malacostraca" family="Gammaridae" genus="Gammarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sepidannus">
<emphasis box="[1139,1296,1117,1141]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">G. sepidannus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it differs by having a long eye, less setose flagellum of antenna 
<number box="[726,742,1153,1177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="2.0">2</number>
, and shorter antennal gland cone (
<emphasis box="[1126,1170,1153,1177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">ibid</emphasis>
. 
<figureCitation box="[1184,1248,1153,1177]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1569,1592]" captionTargetBox="[196,1361,337,1474]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,261,1546]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 1. Distribution map of freshwater Gammarus species in Iran (grey regions indicate high mountainous areas)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205632/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[1235,1248,1153,1177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
